Chapter 10: CTE
Common Table Expression
Problem
Complex query becoming unreadable.
Thinking
Break problem into smaller steps.
Like:
Step 1

Calculate totals.

Step 2

Filter totals.
________________________________________
Example
WITH SalesCTE AS
(
SELECT CustomerID,
SUM(Amount) Sales
FROM Sales
GROUP BY CustomerID
)

SELECT *
FROM SalesCTE
WHERE Sales > 10000;
________________________________________
Chapter 11: Subqueries
Problem
Find employees above average salary.
________________________________________
Thinking
Need average salary first.
Then compare each employee.
One query depends on another.
Use:
Subquery
________________________________________
Solution
SELECT *
FROM Employees
WHERE Salary >
(
SELECT AVG(Salary)
FROM Employees
);
________________________________________
Chapter 12: MERGE
Most Important Data Engineer SQL
Asked in:
✅ ADF
✅ Databricks
✅ Synapse
✅ SQL Server
________________________________________
Problem
Existing table:
101 Ravi
102 Anil
New file:
101 Ravi Kumar

103 Ram
Need:
Update 101

Insert 103
________________________________________
Thinking
Need:
Update Existing
+
Insert New
Use:
MERGE
________________________________________
Solution
MERGE Target t
USING Source s
ON t.ID=s.ID

WHEN MATCHED
THEN UPDATE

WHEN NOT MATCHED
THEN INSERT;
________________________________________
Interview Follow-Up
Q:
Why MERGE?
Answer:
Single statement.

Handles updates and inserts together.
